- *Slow-Paced Breathing, Cold Face Immersion, and Ultra-Low Stroke Rate Rowing — Evidence-Based Protocol Revision and Literature Integration* ([Chapter 17, new/expanded sections: (cert 0.55→0.40 after Ryabkova2024 null finding that ME/CFS does NOT normalize HRV during single-session SPB); `@subsec:cold-face-immersion` cold face immersion with mechanism corrected (vagal+sympathetic co-activation, not pure vagal; 0°C threshold for vagal engagement per Gorini-Pereira 2024; MAP elevation ~23 mmHg per Schlader 2016), safety warning (contraindicated in POTS/s ympathetic-dominant conditions), tVNS comparison (CFI stronger but less selective); expanded `@spec:rowing-stroke-rate-dial` rowing biomechanics (cert 0.40→0.25 after finding zero data below 20 spm, C2 PM5 accuracy invalid below 30W, flywheel momentum resets below ~12 spm per Martindale 1984); Chapter 14b, tVNS section expanded with expected outcomes and timelines (Teixeira 2024 RCT: 8--10 bpm tilt test reduction at 2 months); Chapter 17, side-sleeping glymphatic section (cert 0.68→0.55, added expected outcomes and time-to-benefit); Chapter 17, tVNS immunomodulation section expanded with expected outcomes and timeline; references.bib, 22 new entries (Laborde2022, Lehrer2014, Shao2024, Zaccaro2018, Gerritsen2018, Kromenacker2018, Laborde2019, Sakakibara2020, SevozCouche2022, Jayawardena2020, Ryabkova2024, Heath1990, Kinoshita2006, AlHaddad2010, Shamsuzzaman2014, Schlader2016, GoriniPereira2024, Panneton2020, Held2020, Treff2022, Martindale1984, Sanderson1986, Hofmijster2009, Kane2013, Boyas2006); Appendix H, 3 new annotated bibliography sections: "Slow-Paced Breathing -- Vagal Priming for Sleep and Autonomic Function" (9 entries), "Cold Face Immersion -- Diving Reflex Vagal Activation" (9 entries), "Rowing Biomechanics -- Ultra-Low Stroke Rate in Exercise-Intolerant Populations" (10 entries); hypothesis trees, 3 new subtree files (slow-breathing-vagal 18 nodes, cold-face-immersion 12 nodes, rowing-biomechanics 11 nodes); content-staging, 3 new brainstorms (59+44+41 = 144 ideas) and 3 new literature summaries; review: 6a convergence (2 rounds), 6b adversarial (6 personas, 22 genuine findings, 6 fixes), 6c typst review complete]): Comprehensive evidence-based revision of three non-pharmacological lifestyle interventions that were previously underspecified. Key findings: (1) 4-7-8 breathing has zero peer-reviewed evidence -- the mechanism is inherited from the SPB literature; Ryabkova et al. (2024) demonstrated ME/CFS patients do NOT normalize HRV during single-session SPB, constituting the primary experimental constraint. (2) Cold face immersion produces coordinated vagal + sympathetic co-activation (MAP rise ~23 mmHg, vasoconstriction 44--72%), not pure vagal activation; vagal engagement (RMSSD/HF-HRV increase) requires 0°C ice-water -- tap-water-temperature face splashing is mechanistically distinct and does not engage the vagal component of the diving reflex. (3) Rowing stroke-rate-as-dial at 5--10 spm operates in a complete data void -- the lowest published data is at 20 spm (245 W, Held 2020); per-stroke force is 2--4× higher at 5 spm than 18 spm due to flywheel momentum reset (Martindale 1984); C2 PM5 power accuracy is unvalidated below ~30 W with start-stroke errors of 10--70% (Treff 2022). Clinical implications: tVNS is the better-evidenced vagal stimulation alternative; side-sleeping remains the highest-certainty, lowest-risk sleep intervention (cert 0.55, passive, zero cost). _Motivated by:_ literature gaps identified in the Phase 1 systematic review -- critical biomechanical and autonomic physiology constraints that substantially modify the risk-benefit profile of all three interventions in the ME/CFS population.
